<br>
I have a lvl 52 chanter and need some guidance on a couple things.<br>
<br>
First off, I'm trying to gear her up in order to max cha/int.  Any recommendations on gear? She is sitting about 200/200 atm, but I want to try to maximize her slots if I can.  I am holding out for lvls since I do have a few pieces of ornate (gloves, sleeves, pants) that I will turn in as soon as she's old enough.  (I've heard conflicting stories regarding turn-in lvls on this, so any guidance here is appreciated as well. She doesn't have any PoP flags atm.)  I'm not in a position to really get high-end stuff with my guild, so this would have to be questable/baz type items.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I'm trying to find a decent solo spot for her.  Any suggestions on areas that give a goodly amt of exp at this lvl?<br>
<br>
Thanks for your help!<br>
<br>
Lana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=breezantheold>Breezan the Old</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(11/17/03 1:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the pros...equip/exp stuff</span><hr size=1> Tough questions here, Lana......gear wise, int is extermely easy to max, especially if you eventually get into some of the pop pre elemental zones. Cha poses a bit more of an issue, best thing i could tell you there is LDoN, and look at some of the armor types and augs.<br>
<br>
You can kinda trade off your cha for other stats/resists items as cha really only comes into play if you charm/pacify a lot. Other wise it really doesn't do much for us ( although I like to think otherwise, I am still of the old school that likes to see my cha as high as possible).<br>
<br>
As for a solo spot, I pretty much grouped my way through 65 with the help of a guild as well.  I do more charm soloing now then when i was in the 50's albeit mostly for farming ingredients for trade skills.<br>
<br>
If you can afford ornate that is a good way of going and like i said LDoN armor with augs can go a long way to maxing those stats.  If I am going to be doing a lot of pacifying then i may swap out my range slot item for my JC trophy and max my cha other wise, even for charming higher level stuff (60+) I have found that getting your Total domination aa max and have a cha of 250 + generally suffices.<br>
<br>
Hope this somewhat helps, as you get through the higher levels of the game, the equipment you tend to acquire has both cha and int so it is usually not too hard to max both, if you are trying to max them at your current level without buffs you may run into trouble find the appropriate gear.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp and mo.<br>
<br>
